A failure by a party (Party A

For the purposes of this summary of the principles I shall assume that Party A is female, and Party B is male. The principles of course apply equally irrespective of the genders of the parties.
		  ) to explain the basis of a claim, or a failure by her to comply with the court’s procedural directions aimed, inter alia at requiring her to give a true picture of her circumstances, will have the effect of preventing the other party (Party B) from gaining a clear view of the financial landscape and is tantamount to a refusal by Party A to negotiate openly.
